                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested"><name>Κλωδι<supplied reason="lost">αν</supplied>ὸς</name></persName>
                    <lb n="2"/><choice><orig>κὲ</orig><reg>καὶ</reg></choice> <persName type="attested"><name>Μοῦσα</name></persName>
                    <lb n="3"/>σὺν πεδί<unclear>ο</unclear><supplied reason="lost">ις</supplied>
                    <lb n="4"/>ὑπὲρ εὐχῆς
                    <lb n="5"/> ἐπ<supplied reason="lost">οίησ</supplied>αν
                </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp>
                    <app><note>Text of Muscolino</note></app>
                    <app loc="6"><note>Kaibel after Morso: ἐπέθηκαν</note></app>
                </listApp>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#JP">
                <p>Klodianos and Mousa, together with their offspring, made this on account of a prayer/vow</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Muscolino offers a revised reading, based upon a newly discovered apograph of 1810 from the time of the discovery, which diverges from that, based upon a separate apograph, of Morso 1823. Muscolino concludes that the text was incised on a marble plaque as part of a decorative stone floor, rather than being a mosaic text.</p>
            </div>
